<tmc-service-paragraph><pub id="RM25T0E"><servcat id="_51"><name>Engine / Hybrid System</name><section id="_029760"><name>1VD-FTV ENGINE CONTROL</name><ttl id="_0309414"><name>ECD SYSTEM(w/o EGR System)</name><para category="C" id="RM100000001K9FZ"><dtccode>P0122</dtccode><dtcname>Throttle / Pedal Position Sensor / Switch "A" Circuit Low Input</dtcname><dtccode>P0123</dtccode><dtcname>Throttle / Pedal Position Sensor / Switch "A" Circuit High Input</dtcname><dtccode>P0222</dtccode><dtcname>Throttle / Pedal Position Sensor / Switch "B" Circuit Low Input</dtcname><dtccode>P0223</dtccode><dtcname>Throttle / Pedal Position Sensor / Switch "B" Circuit High Input</dtcname><subpara category="03" id="RM100000001K9FZ_01"><name>DESCRIPTION</name><content5><ptxt>The throttle position sensor is mounted on the diesel throttle body and detects the opening angle of the throttle valve. This sensor is an electronic sensor and uses Hall-effect elements.</ptxt><ptxt>When the throttle valve is fully closed, a voltage of approximately 0.7 V is applied to terminal VLU of the ECM. The voltage applied to terminal VLU of the ECM increases in proportion to the opening angle of the throttle valve and becomes approximately 3.5 to 4.0 V when the throttle valve is fully opened.</ptxt><ptxt>The ECM determines the vehicle's driving conditions from the signals input to its terminal VLU.</ptxt><figure translate="E" type="1"><graphic graphicname="A128639E01" height="3.812598425in" width="7.168479331in"/></figure><table pgwide="1" type="dtc-explan-table"><tgroup cols="6"><colspec colname="1" colwidth="0.71in"/><colspec colname="2" colwidth="1.42in"/><colspec colname="3" colwidth="1.77in"/><colspec colname="4" colwidth="1.77in"/><colspec colname="5" colwidth="0.71in"/><colspec colname="6" colwidth="0.70in"/><thead><row><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>DTC No.</ptxt></entry><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>Detection Item</ptxt></entry><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>DTC Detection Condition</ptxt></entry><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>Trouble Area</ptxt></entry><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>MIL</ptxt></entry><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>Memory</ptxt></entry></row></thead><tbody><row><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="dtc-code"><ptxt>P0122</ptxt></data-name></entry><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="detect-item"><ptxt>Throttle / Pedal Position Sensor / Switch "A" Circuit Low Input</ptxt></data-name></entry><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="dtc-detect-cond"><ptxt>Throttle position sensor (for Bank 1) output (VLU) is less than 0.2 V</ptxt><ptxt>(1 trip detection logic)</ptxt></data-name></entry><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="trouble-area"><list1 type="unordered"><item><ptxt>Throttle position sensor (for Bank 1)</ptxt></item><item><ptxt>Open or short in VLU circuit</ptxt></item><item><ptxt>Open in VC circuit</ptxt></item><item><ptxt>ECM</ptxt></item></list1></data-name></entry><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="mil"><ptxt>Comes on</ptxt></data-name></entry><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="memory"><ptxt>DTC stored</ptxt></data-name></entry></row><row><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="dtc-code"><ptxt>P0123</ptxt></data-name></entry><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="detect-item"><ptxt>Throttle / Pedal Position Sensor / Switch "A" Circuit High Input</ptxt></data-name></entry><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="dtc-detect-cond"><ptxt>Throttle position sensor (for Bank 1) output (VLU) is more than 4.8 V</ptxt><ptxt>(1 trip detection logic)</ptxt></data-name></entry><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="trouble-area"><list1 type="unordered"><item><ptxt>Throttle position sensor (for Bank 1)</ptxt></item><item><ptxt>Open in E2 circuit</ptxt></item><item><ptxt>VC and VLU circuits are short-circuited</ptxt></item><item><ptxt>ECM</ptxt></item></list1></data-name></entry><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="mil"><ptxt>Comes on</ptxt></data-name></entry><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="memory"><ptxt>DTC stored</ptxt></data-name></entry></row><row><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="dtc-code"><ptxt>P0222</ptxt></data-name></entry><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="detect-item"><ptxt>Throttle / Pedal Position Sensor / Switch "B" Circuit Low Input</ptxt></data-name></entry><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="dtc-detect-cond"><ptxt>Throttle position sensor (for Bank 2) output (VLU2) is less than 0.2 V</ptxt><ptxt>(1 trip detection logic)</ptxt></data-name></entry><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="trouble-area"><list1 type="unordered"><item><ptxt>Throttle position sensor (for Bank 2)</ptxt></item><item><ptxt>Open or short in VLU2 circuit</ptxt></item><item><ptxt>Open in VC circuit</ptxt></item><item><ptxt>ECM</ptxt></item></list1></data-name></entry><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="mil"><ptxt>Comes on</ptxt></data-name></entry><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="memory"><ptxt>DTC stored</ptxt></data-name></entry></row><row><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="dtc-code"><ptxt>P0223</ptxt></data-name></entry><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="detect-item"><ptxt>Throttle / Pedal Position Sensor / Switch "B" Circuit High Input</ptxt></data-name></entry><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="dtc-detect-cond"><ptxt>Throttle position sensor (for Bank 2) output (VLU2) is more than 4.8 V</ptxt><ptxt>(1 trip detection logic)</ptxt></data-name></entry><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="trouble-area"><list1 type="unordered"><item><ptxt>Throttle position sensor (for Bank 2)</ptxt></item><item><ptxt>Open in E2 circuit</ptxt></item><item><ptxt>VC and VLU2 circuits are short-circuited</ptxt></item><item><ptxt>ECM</ptxt></item></list1></data-name></entry><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="mil"><ptxt>Comes on</ptxt></data-name></entry><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="memory"><ptxt>DTC stored</ptxt></data-name></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></content5></subpara><subpara category="03" id="RM100000001K9FZ_07"><name>CONFIRMATION DRIVING PATTERN</name><content5><table pgwide="1"><tgroup cols="2"><colspec colname="col1" colwidth="2.12in"/><colspec colname="col2" colwidth="4.96in"/><thead><row><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>DTC No.</ptxt></entry><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>DTC Detection Drive Pattern</ptxt></entry></row></thead><tbody><row><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>P0122</ptxt><ptxt>P0123</ptxt><ptxt>P0222</ptxt><ptxt>P0223</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle"><ptxt>Ignition switch ON for 3 seconds</ptxt></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></content5></subpara><subpara category="03" id="RM100000001K9FZ_02"><name>MONITOR DESCRIPTION</name><content5><ptxt>When the output voltage of the throttle position sensor deviates from the normal operating range (between 0.2 V and 4.8 V) for more than 3 seconds, the ECM interprets this as a malfunction of the sensor circuit and illuminates the MIL.</ptxt><figure translate="E" type="1"><graphic graphicname="C129051E09" height="3.812598425in" width="7.168479331in"/></figure></content5></subpara><subpara category="03" id="RM100000001K9FZ_03"><name>WIRING DIAGRAM</name><content5><figure translate="E" type="1"><graphic graphicname="A165736E17" height="5.838041339in" width="7.168479331in"/></figure></content5></subpara><subpara category="10" id="RM100000001K9FZ_04"><name>CAUTION / NOTICE / HINT</name><content5><atten3><ptxt>After replacing the ECM, the new ECM needs registration (See page <mlink><xref href="RM100000001K9F9" label="Seep00001" term-id-from="005"/></mlink>) and initialization (See page <mlink><xref href="RM100000001K9FA" label="Seep00002" term-id-from="005"/></mlink>).</ptxt></atten3><atten4><ptxt>Read freeze frame data using the GTS. Freeze frame data records the engine condition when malfunctions are detected. When troubleshooting, freeze frame data can help determine if the vehicle was moving or stationary, if the engine was warmed up or not, and other data from the time the malfunction occurred.</ptxt></atten4></content5></subpara><subpara category="01" id="RM100000001K9FZ_06"><name>PROCEDURE</name><testgrp cellposition="1-1" id="RM100000001K9FZ_06_0001"><testtitle>CHECK HARNESS AND CONNECTOR (THROTTLE POSITION SENSOR - ECM)</testtitle><content6><test1><ptxt>Disconnect the throttle position sensor connector.</ptxt><figure translate="C" type="1"><graphic graphicname="A311462C04" height="4.677165354in" width="3.434793307in"/><callout><table pgwide="0" type="caption-table"><tgroup cols="2"><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="0.69in"/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="2.75in"/><tbody><row><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>*1</ptxt></entry><entry><ptxt>for Bank 1</ptxt></entry></row><row><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>*2</ptxt></entry><entry><ptxt>for Bank 2</ptxt></entry></row><row><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>*a</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle"><ptxt>Front view of wire harness connector</ptxt><ptxt>(to Throttle Position Sensor)</ptxt></entry></row><row><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>*b</ptxt></entry><entry><ptxt>Front view of wire harness connector</ptxt><ptxt>(to ECM)</ptxt></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></callout></figure></test1><test1><ptxt>Disconnect the ECM connector.</ptxt></test1><test1><ptxt>Measure the resistance according to the value(s) in the table below.</ptxt><spec type="resistance"><title>Standard Resistance</title><table><title>for Bank 1</title><tgroup cols="3"><colspec colname="col1" colwidth="1.38in"/><colspec colname="col2" colwidth="1.38in"/><colspec colname="col3" colwidth="1.37in"/><thead><row><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>Tester Connection</ptxt></entry><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>Condition</ptxt></entry><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>Specified Condition</ptxt></entry></row></thead><tbody><row><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>C50-1 (VC) - C39-91 (VCVL)</ptxt></entry><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>Always</ptxt></entry><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>Below 1 Ω</ptxt></entry></row><row><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>C50-3 (VTA) - C39-93 (VLU)</ptxt></entry><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>Always</ptxt></entry><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>Below 1 Ω</ptxt></entry></row><row><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>C50-2 (E2) - C39-92 (EVLU)</ptxt></entry><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>Always</ptxt></entry><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>Below 1 Ω</ptxt></entry></row><row><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>C50-1 (VC) or C39-91 (VCVL) - Body ground</ptxt></entry><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>Always</ptxt></entry><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>10 kΩ or higher</ptxt></entry></row><row><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>C50-3 (VTA) or C39-93 (VLU) - Body ground</ptxt></entry><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>Always</ptxt></entry><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>10 kΩ or higher</ptxt></entry></row><row><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>C50-2 (E2) or C39-92 (EVLU) - Body ground</ptxt></entry><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>Always</ptxt></entry><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>10 kΩ or higher</ptxt></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table><table><title>for Bank 2</title><tgroup cols="3"><colspec colname="col1" colwidth="1.38in"/><colspec colname="col2" colwidth="1.38in"/><colspec colname="col3" colwidth="1.37in"/><thead><row><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>Tester Connection</ptxt></entry><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>Condition</ptxt></entry><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>Specified Condition</ptxt></entry></row></thead><tbody><row><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>C65-1 (VC) - C39-91 (VCVL)</ptxt></entry><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>Always</ptxt></entry><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>Below 1 Ω</ptxt></entry></row><row><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>C65-3 (VTA) - C39-103 (VLU2)</ptxt></entry><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>Always</ptxt></entry><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>Below 1 Ω</ptxt></entry></row><row><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>C65-2 (E2) - C39-92 (EVLU)</ptxt></entry><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>Always</ptxt></entry><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>Below 1 Ω</ptxt></entry></row><row><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>C65-1 (VC) or C39-91 (VCVL) - Body ground</ptxt></entry><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>Always</ptxt></entry><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>10 kΩ or higher</ptxt></entry></row><row><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>C65-3 (VTA) or C39-103 (VLU2) - Body ground</ptxt></entry><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>Always</ptxt></entry><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>10 kΩ or higher</ptxt></entry></row><row><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>C65-2 (E2) or C39-92 (EVLU) - Body ground</ptxt></entry><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>Always</ptxt></entry><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>10 kΩ or higher</ptxt></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></spec></test1><spec type="other"><title>Result</title><table><tgroup cols="1"><colspec colname="col1" colwidth="4.13in"/><thead><row><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>Proceed to</ptxt></entry></row></thead><tbody><row><entry align="center" valign="middle"><judge-value label="1"><ptxt>OK</ptxt></judge-value></entry></row><row><entry align="center" valign="middle"><judge-value label="2"><ptxt>NG</ptxt></judge-value></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></spec></content6><results><result cellposition="1-1" label="1"><action actiontype="next" cellposition="2-1" childid="RM100000001K9FZ_06_0003"/></result><result cellposition="1-3" label="2"><action actiontype="end" cellposition="2-3"><actiontitle>REPAIR OR REPLACE HARNESS OR CONNECTOR</actiontitle><content6/></action></result></results></testgrp><testgrp cellposition="2-1" id="RM100000001K9FZ_06_0003"><testtitle>CHECK ECM TERMINAL VOLTAGE (VC TERMINAL)</testtitle><content6><test1><ptxt>Disconnect the throttle position sensor connector.</ptxt><figure translate="C" type="1"><graphic graphicname="A165737C03" height="3.434793307in" width="3.434793307in"/><callout><table pgwide="0" type="caption-table"><tgroup cols="2"><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="0.69in"/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="2.75in"/><tbody><row><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>*1</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle"><ptxt>for Bank 1</ptxt></entry></row><row><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>*2</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle"><ptxt>for Bank 2</ptxt></entry></row><row><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>*a</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle"><ptxt>Front view of wire harness connector</ptxt><ptxt>(to Throttle Position Sensor)</ptxt></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></callout></figure></test1><test1><ptxt>Measure the voltage according to the value(s) in the table below.</ptxt><spec type="voltage"><title>Standard Voltage</title><table><title>for Bank 1</title><tgroup cols="3"><colspec colname="col1" colwidth="1.38in"/><colspec colname="col2" colwidth="1.38in"/><colspec colname="col3" colwidth="1.37in"/><thead><row><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>Tester Connection</ptxt></entry><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>Switch Condition</ptxt></entry><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>Specified Condition</ptxt></entry></row></thead><tbody><row><ent